body.description: The perfect tablet for entertainment on the go, the Lenovo Tab M9 features a 9” LCD display and weighs less than a pound. Dual speakers provide crystal clear sound to further enhance a stunningly mobile cinematic experience. Inside, you’ll find a powerful octa-core chip and up to 32GB of storage. With a long lasting 5100 mAh battery, stream your favorite movies and shows all day without having to worry about finding a power outlet. Running the Android 12 operating system, the Tab M9 offers Bluetooth connectivity, a USB-C charging port and a 3.5mm audio jack. Use the front or rear camera to take photos or enjoy a family video chat, with dual speakers providing crisp, clear sound. You can even log in quickly and easily with Face Unlock.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little tablet
reviews.reviewText: Since I have a Lenovo laptop, I figure I would give this tablet a try. So far so good. It's not too heavy to hold and the screen is nice. I like that it is a 9in screen. It isn't super fast but it isn't slow either. It came with 32gb of storage, I would have like more. I would recommend this tablet for anyone on a budget.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent, Affordably Priced, Budget Tablet
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to replace an aging Lenovo tablet I’d purchased 4 years ago during the pandemic. It was easy to set up, and I synced it to another android device. I’ll primarily use this for watching Disney Plus or Netflix, reading, or playing an occasional game while I’m on the road and traveling for work. Doesn’t have a ton of storage space, but it suits my needs. Battery charges quickly and has decent battery life. You can certainly buy a much higher quality tablet or an iPad, but then again, you’re spending a lot more for those. Pictured with the Seymac stock Lenovo M9 tablet cover - an imitation Otterbox, of sorts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for price.
reviews.reviewText: This review is for the Lenovo Tab M9. I noticed the reviews seem to combine both the M8 and M9. As far as the M9, I purchased the tablet during prime day for $109. For the price, you will not get a better tablet. Sure, Amazon fire tablets sometimes are cheaper, but do not offer full access to the google play store and performance. The M9 offers good performance for the price. Web browsing, and light multitasking with split screen is possible. Also, some light gaming is possible with the right settings. Of course, when compared to an iPad mini 6 (which I own) or a more expensive android tablet, the M9 will be beaten. However, I recommend the M9 if you need an entry level tablet with full access to the google play store. The screen is plenty bright and it has good built quality.As far as the included folio case, the magnets are not very strong, so it does not stay closed. Also the screen protector is plastic and flimsy. I ended up purchasing a glass tempered screen protector and am using the folio case until more are released with better form factors. Skip the M8, which is abysmally slow now and the screen is dim (I owned the third generation M8). Just be aware that the internal storage of the M9 is limited, so if you have a lot of apps, you may use up a lot of storage quick. I use it mainly to stream YouTube, Netflix, etc and web browsing. I’ve also used it to video conference through zoom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic for the price point
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as an e-reader and for the occasional streaming/light gaming. I use the app ReadEra (not a fan of Kindle) and I couldn't be happier. With the brightness turned to minimal (you don't need much for reading), I get 20+ hours easily. Streaming gets me between 3-6 depending on brightness. The included case is great quality for protection against scratches in your bag, ease of holding, and auto sleep when closed - but in no way is this going to save your tablet from a fall off the table.*This tablet is going to need a couple minutes booting to full speed when powering up. This isn't the case when waking form sleep mode - it's ready to go automatically. But expect some patience when cycling the power.*This tablet should be good for live android updates until at least next year, but runs great out of the box for the basics.*I've also dabbled with some low end retri emulation (GBA, SNES, and even PS1) - all working great especially when connected to power. The bluetooth pairs with a controller no problem.I'd buy this tablet again, especially if its on sale.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The GEM of RETRO Emulation
reviews.reviewText: This Tablet is a dream come true of the most amazing performance, PSP games work flawlessly.. with the correct emulation settings you can emulate any N64 video game to perfection 250x320 resolution.. better than console performance, Game Boy advance, NES, Sega Genesis..games are amazing.. MD.emu. NES emu. GBA.emu.. I have uploaded my Library of Video game Treasures that I run on this Masterpiece of technology, FAST charging, Battery life, I've had it on Super Smash Bros N64 since 6 am and it's 12:40 pm and the battery is at 93%. Picture quality?. Well I put the brightness on 20% 25%.. in the dark in dim it all the way LOW.. this is the perfect emulation device.. you can Bluetooth up 4 Sega 6 button Fight pad controllers. And play 4 player like a breeze on smash bros. amazing built in speakers. Amazing quality. It's like a mini Alien spaceship.. you may need a game booster app for N64 games for optimization.. runs God of War Ghost of Sparta Flawlessly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have not had an android tablet in quite yet some time. I tried this one out and it was everything I was hoping for… everything but one major flaw.On the good side it was fast, smooth, great picture quality. It connected fine to all my other devices and it is, in my opinion, the perfect size for a tablet.Unfortunately I did not know that android tablets have started to go the apple route and do not allow you to increase your device storage space. You can mount an SD for extra storage, but not to increase the devices internal storage. This means that you cannot put apps on the SD and with the newer android OS being close to 15gig on it’s own and the files it creates upon starting your storage space is already half gone. That is not sustainable and I’ll be sending it back. It’s very frustrating because aside from that it’s a perfect little tablet for me. Sad day…

reviews.reviewerName: Francisco Javier Zavala de la Torre
reviews.reviewText: Es una tableta económica pero esto no demerita la calidad, excelente en todas sus funcionalidades.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good entry tablet with more than average performance
reviews.reviewText: Good entry tablet with more than average performance

Solo para usar en la escuela, no esperen que sea para trabajo, no tiene el rendimiento ni las dimensiones para dibujar, manejar documentos y tener varias aplicaciones ejecutándose, solo es para multimedia y algún otro juego o como lo dije al inicio para un niño de primaria o secundaria que necesita ver correos, tener sesiones por zoom, anotar en algún documento, algo muy básico. Se aumenta la memoria, viene con una mica y una carcasa de buena calidad.

Llegó en perfectas condiciones, ahorita al configurar y pedir bajar varias apps y al mismo tiempo ver otras configuración se traba... así que esta tablet es solo para ver streaming de cámaras y películas/series, definitivamente no es para juegos, se le agradece a la marca que tenga el detalle de agregar cargador, case, mica protectora (aunque es de mala calidad) si no eres quisquilloso con pequeñas burbujas o basurita que pueda meterse en el proceso todo perfecto, la pantalla si deja huella marcada así que definitivamente la mica ayuda bastante
